.TH BCOPY 3 2013-10-22 "Linux" "Linux Programmer's Manual"
.SH NAME
bcopy \- copy byte sequence
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <strings.h>
.sp
.BI "void bcopy(const void *" src ", void *" dest ", size_t " n );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR bcopy ()
function copies
.I n
bytes from
.I src
to
.IR dest .
The result is correct, even when both areas overlap.
.SH RETURN VALUE
None.
.SH ATTRIBUTES
.SS Multithreading (see pthreads(7))
The
.BR bcopy ()
function is thread-safe.
.SH CONFORMING TO
4.3BSD.
This function is deprecated (marked as LEGACY in POSIX.1-2001): use
.BR memcpy (3)
or
.BR memmove (3)
in new programs.
Note that the first two arguments
are interchanged for
.BR memcpy (3)
and
.BR memmove (3).
POSIX.1-2008 removes the specification of
.BR bcopy ().
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR memccpy (3),
.BR memcpy (3),
.BR memmove (3),
.BR strcpy (3),
.BR strncpy (3)
